Step 1 : Create the view
from django.shortcuts import render

def privacy_policy(request):
    return render(request, "privacy.html")

Step 2 : Add URL mapping
from django.urls import path
from . import views

urlpatterns = [
    path("privacy/", views.privacy_policy, name="privacy"),
]

Step 3 : Create template
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
   <title>Privacy Policy</title>
</head>
<body style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; max-width: 800px; margin: auto; padding: 20px; line-height: 1.6;">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Your privacy is important to us. This policy explain how we handle your information,</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect personal details such as your name, email address, and any information you provide throughour contact form or order syatem.</p>

    <h2>How we use your information</h2>
    <p>YOur informationis used only to provide our services, respond to inquiries, and improve your experience.</p>

    <h2>Data sharing</h2>
    <p>We donot sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties, except when required by the law.</p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>We may use cookies to enhance your browsing experience, You can disbale cookies in your browser settings.</p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>We take appropriate steps to protect your information from unauthorized access and misuse.</p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us through our contact page.</p>
</body>
</html>